conbody.p: Create an xline (infinitely long line) from a combination of options point, direction, and angle.

section.title: Methods to begin an xline
section.p: There are six methods to begin creating an xline:
You can continue adding unlimited xlines until you press Enter to end the command.

dlentry.dd: Begin creating an xline by specifying a point on the xline then:
Specify the direction of the xline from the starting point.
Begin creating an xline parallel to the x-axis then:
Specify a point on the xline.
Begin creating an xline parallel to the y-axis then:
Specify a point on the xline.
Begin creating an xline based on an angle then:
Specify the angle of the xline.
Additional option: [Reference]
Specify a point on the xline.
Begin creating an xline which bisects two imaginary lines then:
Specify a point at the vertex of the two imaginary lines.
Additional option: [Entity]
Specify a point to define the first imaginary line. The vertex is used as the other point.
Specify a point to define the second imaginary line. The vertex is used as the other point.
Begin creating an xline parallel to a line or polyline segment then:

dlentry.dt: Set offset distance for parallel infinite line
dlentry.dd: Specify the offset distance for the xline.
Additional option: [Through point]

dlentry.dt: Select entity for parallel infinite line
dlentry.dd: Select a line or polyline segment from which to offset the xline.
Specify the side on which to place the xline.

section.title: Options within the XLINE command
section.p: After you begin creating an xline, the following option may be available:

dlentry.dd: Select an entity to use as a reference angle then:
Specify the angle to place the xline relative to the selected entity.

Select a line, arc or polyline segment to bisect. When you select a line or polyline segment, the command draws the xline perpendicular to the segment’s midpoint. When you select an arc or polyarc, the command draws the xline perpendicular to the arc’s center and point.
This option works with splined polylines, but not with spline entities.
Specify a point through which to draw the xline

dlentry.dt: Select entity for parallel infinite line
dlentry.dd: Select an entity to which the xline should be parallel.
Specify a point through which to draw the xline.
